<i>Current address 67 Maple Drive,
Bloomfield Hills, Michigan.</i>

19:34.840 --> 19:36.559
Story time. It's lunch.

19:36.720 --> 19:38.359
- We want a story.
- Yeah, man.

19:38.520 --> 19:40.079
Yeah, man. Let's hear something.

19:40.280 --> 19:42.397
Then a story you shall have.

19:47.000 --> 19:50.152
A story about...loving.

19:50.320 --> 19:54.997
There was a boy who fell deeply,

19:55.160 --> 19:57.880
passionately in love
with a girl.

19:58.040 --> 20:02.193
Certain natural processes
took place...

20:04.200 --> 20:08.592
..and she found herself
with child and yearned to marry.

20:09.600 --> 20:13.037
But the year was 1959

20:13.200 --> 20:15.715
and they lived
in the state of Virginia

20:15.880 --> 20:17.519
where it was against the law.

20:17.680 --> 20:20.991
He was white and she was black.

20:21.160 --> 20:22.799
So they went up
to our nation's capital

20:22.960 --> 20:25.077
to make her an honest woman.

20:27.240 --> 20:29.755
When they returned,

20:29.920 --> 20:33.516
they were arrested
because they were married.

20:34.640 --> 20:36.279
They were loving.

20:36.440 --> 20:38.113
Did they fight it?

20:38.280 --> 20:42.069
To the Supreme Court, June 1967.

20:42.240 --> 20:43.879
They won.

20:44.040 --> 20:47.829
That's why no-one can tell us
who to marry today

20:48.000 --> 20:49.639
because of loving -

20:49.800 --> 20:52.235
Mildred and Richard Loving.

20:52.400 --> 20:54.631
True story.

20:54.800 --> 20:57.918
Eight years later,

20:58.080 --> 21:00.037
a drunk driver hit their car.

21:01.680 --> 21:03.956
Richard was killed,

21:04.120 --> 21:05.918
Mildred lost an eye.

21:07.920 --> 21:09.718
She never remarried.

21:13.600 --> 21:17.389
I've spent a good deal of time
on my own...

21:19.000 --> 21:21.037
..separate and apart...

21:22.120 --> 21:24.396
..wondering if I was someone
worth loving.

21:25.800 --> 21:29.271
I'm pretty sure most of us felt
that way at one time or another.

21:30.760 --> 21:33.673
Then the other day
it occurred to me,

21:33.840 --> 21:37.072
maybe I'm the one
who needs to do the loving.

21:39.840 --> 21:41.638
And you know what?

21:43.280 --> 21:47.752
I haven't felt alone,
separate or apart since.

22:06.960 --> 22:09.236
Hey.

22:13.120 --> 22:15.112
Beautiful service.

22:15.280 --> 22:17.397
Very moving.

22:17.600 --> 22:20.479
I saw you speaking to Destiny
in the receiving line.

22:20.640 --> 22:23.712
Oh, yeah.
I never know what to say.

22:23.880 --> 22:29.512
You know, death being what it is
and so forth.

22:30.600 --> 22:34.514
"Oh, he's in a better place"
seems overused.

22:38.000 --> 22:41.118
I spoke to her
and she told me what you said.

22:42.240 --> 22:44.391
Seemed to really land with her.

22:44.560 --> 22:48.793
- In a good way.
- Yeah?

22:50.400 --> 22:54.280
Oh, well... Well, that's...

22:54.440 --> 22:56.159
That's great.

22:56.320 --> 22:58.357
To be honest,
I was a little worried.

22:58.560 --> 23:00.517
Yeah? About what?

23:00.680 --> 23:03.070
Eh, you know, just what I said.

23:04.200 --> 23:06.396
Really? It sounded good.

23:07.400 --> 23:08.914
Which part?

23:14.480 --> 23:16.472
Shit.

23:16.640 --> 23:19.280
Look, man,
I really don't have time...

23:19.440 --> 23:21.272
What did you tell her?

23:21.440 --> 23:23.159
I don't know.

23:23.320 --> 23:25.277
Just that he was a hero.

23:25.440 --> 23:27.272
- A hero?
- Yeah. I don't know.

23:27.440 --> 23:29.955
Something... That he died
a hero. That's it. That's it.

23:30.120 --> 23:31.713
We've been saying
that we don't know anything.

23:31.880 --> 23:33.519
- Now because of you,
she knows we're lying. -Shit.

23:33.720 --> 23:35.313
- I'm sorry.
- Oh. You're sorry?

23:35.480 --> 23:37.358
- Like that fucking matters now?!
- Alright, I'll fix it.

23:37.560 --> 23:41.031
- How? -I...I don't know. Just...
Alright, give me a minute.

23:41.200 --> 23:43.032
- I'll think of something.
- No, no. You don't do anything.

23:43.200 --> 23:44.873
You don't talk to anyone,
you don't do anything.

23:45.040 --> 23:46.838
Just...just don't.

23:57.880 --> 23:59.553
I don't know why
I'm poring over these files

23:59.720 --> 24:01.552
because nothing in them
is going to help us find

24:01.720 --> 24:03.359
your granddaughter...unless...

24:03.520 --> 24:05.352
Where's...where's the pendant?

24:06.640 --> 24:09.792
Chango. I left it right there.

24:09.960 --> 24:11.553
I don't know.

24:11.760 --> 24:13.479
Well, you saw me put it down
there, right?

24:13.680 --> 24:15.558
- I don't remember exactly.
- I remember.

24:15.760 --> 24:18.036
I...I left it right there.

24:20.400 --> 24:23.518
Oh, God. Somebody broke in.

24:23.680 --> 24:26.240
I don't see any signs
of forced entry.

24:26.440 --> 24:28.033
I am not imagining this!

24:28.200 --> 24:30.192
- Did you give anyone a key?
- No.

24:30.400 --> 24:32.676
Your daughter,
the guy that she's with.

24:32.840 --> 24:34.479
Isaac, I changed the locks.

24:34.640 --> 24:36.597
It's gotta be around here
someplace.

24:46.880 --> 24:48.837
I'll be right back.

25:12.720 --> 25:14.837
Hello, Dr Deutsch.

25:16.560 --> 25:18.233
Who...who are you?

25:18.400 --> 25:21.120
For our purposes, a man who just
injected naloxone into your IV.

25:21.280 --> 25:23.397
Hence, the immediate
withdrawal reaction

25:23.560 --> 25:27.634
and the resurgent pain caused
by your underlying condition,

25:27.800 --> 25:29.439
end-stage diabetes

25:29.600 --> 25:32.195
with gangrene of the lower
extremities, I gather.

25:33.200 --> 25:35.920
I apologise
for the inconvenience,

25:36.080 --> 25:37.719
but we need to talk.

25:37.880 --> 25:39.473
Who's Dr Deutsch?

25:39.680 --> 25:41.319
- I'm Richard Auschlander.
- Of course you are.

25:41.480 --> 25:43.551
When you were in Deutschland,
you were Deutsch,

25:43.720 --> 25:46.997
but now you are in Ausland,
so you are an Auslander.

25:48.000 --> 25:49.639
It's clever.

25:49.800 --> 25:53.396
I'm surprised you managed
to slip a pun by the OSS.

25:53.560 --> 25:55.597
What do you want?

25:55.760 --> 25:58.798
I don't care about your service
with Der FÃ¼hrer.

25:58.960 --> 26:00.679
After all, we're both
accomplished in our fields

26:00.840 --> 26:03.912
and understand that scientific
inquiry knows no partisanship.

26:04.120 --> 26:07.397
I need to find
one of our colleagues.

26:07.560 --> 26:11.315
You worked with him
in Plum Island after the war

26:11.480 --> 26:14.200
and knew him as Ryan Dunbrack.

26:16.080 --> 26:17.878
I don't remember.

26:21.040 --> 26:23.236
Then let me clear your mind.

26:45.360 --> 26:47.511
I hope you like roses.

26:51.320 --> 26:53.391
Please, Roman, don't do this...

26:53.560 --> 26:55.199
I don't know exactly why
you're pulling away,

26:55.360 --> 26:57.317
but I'm not gonna let you.

26:57.480 --> 27:00.598
What happened to that security
guard, that is not who I am.

27:00.800 --> 27:02.519
I was just trying
to protect you.

27:02.720 --> 27:05.315
- And however many Hail Marys I
have to say to... -

27:11.200 --> 27:12.998
You two know each other?

27:14.560 --> 27:16.358
Y...you know each other?

27:17.880 --> 27:20.793
This is my mother. This is who
I was warning you about.

27:24.000 --> 27:27.118
Annie, Ochoa.

27:27.280 --> 27:29.351
You don't have a life so
you're rooting around in mine.

27:29.520 --> 27:31.000
It's fucking pathetic.

27:37.960 --> 27:42.159
First Letha, now her?

27:42.320 --> 27:46.280
You're quite the stickman,
fucking two of your sisters.

27:46.440 --> 27:48.636
Only you can't put this one
on me.

28:08.520 --> 28:12.355
I haven't seen him
